Text: Forged from thousands of unclaimed Beta keys
One by one, Kaom slaughtered the weakest tribe\r\nleaders until the others leapt to join his cause.
As battle calms, blood turns to rust.
You are slow, foolish and ignorant.\r\nI am not.
Fear is highly infectious.
A token from the sea\r\nA sign for Kaom\r\nto lead his Karui to Wraeclast.
Danger is the price of wealth.
\"See without doubt, slay without hesitation.\"\r\n- Marceus Lioneye of Sarn
The maidens of court swoon to see\r\nthe challengers crushed at your feet.
Although a great leader during the war,\r\nVoll proved disastrous in times of peace.
Divine intervention feels better\r\nwhen you do it yourself.
\"The wild takes care of its own.\"\r\n- Hyrri of the Karui
In the rift between future and past,\r\nlife passes quickly.
It was a sliver of Malachai's soul\r\nthat animated the first Eternal Guardian.
Centuries of servitude, a day\r\nof glory, an eternity of death.

The mournful music of the strings,
The creaking arch, the arrow sings.
A choking cry, a rattled breath,
The Reaper's Song, the Harp of Death.
Burn to cinders, scar and maim,\r\nRule a world, bathed in flame.
\"The crack of bone, the spray of blood.\r\nIs there sweeter music?\"\r\n- Hrimnor of the Ezomytes.
\"One quick tap is all the persuasion you'll need.\"\r\n- Archbishop Geofri of Phrecia Cathedral
\"Today, clansmen, my sword is my voice!\"\r\n- Rigwald, at the Battle of Glarryn
Stoic visage, icy heart.\r\nLife of sorrow, lived apart.
Where her mouth should have been\r\nthere was only a whirling, black void.
\"Prototype #8 makes it difficult to think negatively, but two fatalities\r\nresulted when a lead researcher used an epithet in its presence.\"
Doryani stumbled into a realm of madness\r\nAnd awoke its Master.
Molten feathers, veiled spark,\r\nHissing arrows from the dark.
Seeing only foot soldiers, the Sarn Knights cast aside\r\ntheir heavy shields... and paid dearly for their mistake.
The breath of life is yours to give.
\"Shoot first, ask no questions.\"\r\n- Karui wisdom
\"In testing, Prototype #9 had no effect on fired arrows. However,\r\nan unknown spell did destroy the entire firing chamber.\"
Never blinking, always watching.\r\n\r\n<default>{This item can be transformed with a Blessing of Chayula}
Hyrri loosed a barrage of arrows,\r\ntipped with a poisoned hatred\r\nonly oppression can ferment.
The warrior who\r\nfears will fall.
\"Useless for our purposes, but perhaps we can sell Prototype #5\r\nto an archmage to fund other experiments.\"
Fairgraves' trusty tricorne accompanied him far across\r\nthe seas, deep under the ground, and even beyond death.
Give of your heated passions.\r\nGive of your cold resolve.\r\nYou will be repaid.
Lift it lightly, don it slow.\r\nThe spikes point out and in, you know.
Asenath's mind was as quick and nimble\r\nas the fingers that drew her bowstring.
\"It takes true strength to hold power,\r\nand my grip grows tighter by the day.\"\r\n - Emperor Chitus
Hrimnor's presence was as cold as ice,\r\nbut his heart burned for vengeance.
We wander to pass time.\r\nWe travel to fulfill.
\"The craven mind is sharp with self interest.\r\nThe honourable mind is much easier to manipulate.\"\r\n - Malachai the Soulless
In the battle for honour, Geofri won.\r\nNot so, the battle for survival.
It is said to make you invisible when the Great\r\nSpirit comes to take you on your final journey.
Wonders abound at death's door.
A mighty beast, a lavish feast.
Stand and lead the righteous pride,\r\nFight till death, never hide.
\"Twelve dead, and the seventh lab cannot be entered for several years.\r\nPrototype #12 is a 'success,' if we can ever reach it.\"
Tempest's power given form,\r\nFlee before the walking storm.
All the world is my home.
Shavronne raced to Brutus' side,\r\nher last hope against the Karui tide.
Blazing body, shining bold.\r\nDance beneath the orb of gold!
The mocking wind, a shielding spell,\r\nThe haunting screams, a maddening hell.
Of ancient giants, none remain,\r\nTheir only trace is timeless pain.
Maligaro operated effortlessly,\r\nwith great speed and terrible consequences.
A soft caress in dead of night,\r\nthat slips about the neck, so tight.
Wealth is not to be borne lightly.
Wealth unspent is wealth wasted.
While Doedre lacked Maligaro's sense of style,\r\nshe surpassed her master in pure malevolence.
A single lightning strike fells a man.\r\nA single knife stroke fells an empire.
Why cling to your sanity? It offers you nothing.\r\nSurrender to me, and I will grant you everything.
The light that reveals is the glare that blinds.

Mindless rage will shake the world,
Cunning lies will bend it.
Reckless haste will break the world,
And into darkness send it.
They say a lifetime of wisdom is carried\r\nin every skin the great beasts shed.
Few men cast a longer shadow\r\n than the Great Meginord of the North.
A large enough debt turns even a friend\r\ninto an enemy, and the Perandus family\r\nhad more debtors than anyone.
Kaom's strength was rivaled only by\r\nthe great Meginord of the north.
By tourney's end, Daresso bled and shivered.\r\nYet even accursed treachery failed to steal the champion's victory.
The Vaal emptied their slaves of beating hearts,\r\nand left a mountain of twitching dead.
Cold, miserable and alone... but alive.
\"With piety and justice.\"\r\n- Perandus family motto
Marceus' unblemished shield is a testament\r\nto his arrogance... and his fate.
Accept your fate, or lie, pretend.\r\nDeath collects you in the end.

His final sensation was of the executioner's blade.
It was not cold, instead warm and reassuring,
murmuring a promise of better times ahead.
Smiling, he returned death's embrace.

She paints her offer in wicked hues
An off-white grin, an elegant bruise.
To the nascent scourge she sings the ruse:
"With me in hand, what else need you use?"
Nothing stops the pain like a courageous rush into battle.
\"Prototype #7 achieved even greater injury responsiveness than expected,\r\nthough at considerable cost to the long-term survival rate of the user.\"
A swift mind solves problems before they occur.
The malice in her gaze froze blood and shattered bone.
Cast into darkness\r\nAnd trapped for a thousand years,\r\nThe lonely moon weeps
\"Should I depart this mortal coil,\r\nso shall all of my treasures.\"\r\n- Atziri, Queen of the Vaal
Swift as thought are the actions of Man \r\nwhen borne on wings of divine providence.
When blood is paid, the weak think twice.
From death springs life.
Lumbering as a sea lion, clumsy as a berry-drunk pigeon. That was Erqi. \r\nIt mattered little. When Erqi's maul fell true, so did its target.
Forged from the blood of countless wars, \r\nits thirst has only begun.
Ride with pride,\r\nstrike with vengeance,\r\nlive with honour.
Fly like a Storm Crow, crush like a Rhoa
Do not let them step on your feet. Keep them at bay.
Unwieldy and garish became graceful\r\nand deadly in Ungil's nimble hands.
\"Recommend further production of Prototype #122. It makes\r\nan ideal weapon for our suppression troops and guards.\"
The wyrm draws warmth from the fires of desire.
The dead man walks where\r\nthe living fear to tread.
\"Outpost Twelve has been abandoned. On the bright side, I expect the plague of apparitions\r\nto serve as ample defence for the relics we left behind.\" \r\n- Administrator Qotra
\"I know how to say 'faster' and 'attack'\r\nin Karui, Marak and Ezo.\"\r\n- Voll of Thebrus
Shavronne's apparel became ever more extravagant\r\nas her body and soul became ever more corrupted.
\"The rain of a thousand quills that whittle\r\npresent into past, life into death.\"\r\n- Rigwald of the Ezomytes
\"How did you manage to lodge arrows in every single test subject\r\nand researcher in Lab Three simultaneously?\" \r\n- Doctor Bircus
\"The Spirit of War knows nothing of good and evil.\r\nIt knows only destruction.\"\r\n- Sekhema Asenath
Swinging through the air, it sings\r\nof sundered, severed, missing things.
Cursed is the star whence it came.

A chilling hush, a scraping sound
Of things no more entombed in ground.
A shambling horde is on its way
To crush the very light of day.
\"Simply incredible. I caught an escaping test subject myself with\r\nswarms of burning skulls. Delightful!\" \r\n- Researcher Olesya
As a soldier you want to get close to enemy archers.\r\nThat is not the case when fighting the Maraketh.
Alive but not unscathed, Victario fled\r\nas slaughter blossomed at the gates.
It is safer to be feared than to be loved.
I'm hiding, yet everyone knows where I am.
The blasted oak stands forever.
He who sows an ember shall reap an inferno.
Mark us with mercy, then press on with care,\r\nExecute us steadily, notch away at our despair.
\"How did you manage to lodge arrows in every single test subject\r\nand researcher in Lab Three simultaneously... again?\" \r\n- Doctor Bircus
The darkest clouds clashed and coupled,\r\ngiving birth to four lightning children of hate.

A mighty bulwark, curved and strong
A dauntless wall, against the throng
All lance and arrow, knocked aside
For rout of foe, for turn of tide.
Its corrugated surface brings a strange tingle\r\nto the fingertips. This is no mere decoration.
When put to the ear it whispers not of\r\nthe sea, but long dead incantations.
Its pleasing sheen remains even in shadow,\r\nas if it were somehow lit from within.
Distilled from naked ambition and unfettered obsession,\r\nthe Allflame emanates a silvern warmth like no other, \r\nand engulfs those moths fool enough to embrace it.
Doctor \"Shaky Hands\" Opden travelled with only the\r\nfinest medicines and antidotes... and a curiously\r\ngenerous supply of opiates.
Maligaro loved his tools, and took great\r\npains to keep them excruciatingly sharp.
The withering glare of corruption, made\r\ncorporeal and pellucid in crystal.
Machinery makes the minions.\r\nMinions make the master.
Essence of pure thaumaturgy.\r\nApply with trepidation.
A craftswoman's ode to\r\nfresh hope, a new love.
Segregated by treachery, this artefact\r\nlongs to be reunited with her sisters.
While this artefact resonates with power,\r\nit is simply a piece in a larger puzzle.
A relic of a sundered relationship,\r\nit awaits reconciliation with its kin.
Though its power has been shared, there\r\nis still more the Apex might unlock.
An open palm raised in peace,\r\ncut down by the slaves of war.
\"A Virtue Gem is a raging thunderstorm imprisoned within a single raindrop.\r\nInfernal Talc simply lets the storm out.\" - Malachai the Soulless
To enter a city's bowels is to be\r\nprivy to its best-kept secrets.
God will only offer the door.\r\nMan must choose whether to open it.
The Emperor honours Hector Titucius as Supreme Servant.\r\n\"Strength in purpose is strength in deed.\"
The Emperor honours Gaius Sentari as Supreme Servant.\r\n\"A man's thoughts are his shackles. A man's thoughts are his wings.\"
The Emperor honours Marceus Lioneye as Supreme Servant.\r\n\"The road to Glory is paved with Sacrifice.\"
To catch an animal, think like an animal.

Shed by the winged beast of night,
A scaly frost-encrusted thorn.
All who feel its wintry light
Shiver in pain at the frozen dawn.
No metal slips as easily through the fingers as gold.
Born from the marriage of ice and sky,\r\nthe aurora evokes both awe and power.
Knowledge brings power, and with power you can\r\ngrab truth by the throat and shape it as you wish.
My Soul is your Strength\r\nMy Price is your Blood
Despair hums, softly, deadly, in the bones of my enemies. \r\nEyes will burn, and souls wither, as they bask in my radiance.
Fear blisters the heart and thins the blood.\r\nFear squeezes lungs and sets the guts to fester.\r\nFear is the wound left untended.

The nobles wanted to take her throne.
She let the peasants take their wealth.
The peasants wanted to take her wealth.
She let the soldiers take their heads.
The soldiers wanted to take her head.
She sat on her throne and wept.
\"As long as I see death in my mirror, so will Wraeclast.\"\r\n- Atziri, Queen of the Vaal
To cease the flow of blood is to \r\nchoke the rain in the very clouds.\r\nBoth life and land feel the thirst.
Centuries of development in steel armoursmithing\r\nturned the armies of the Eternal Empire\r\ninto very effective lightning rods.
To stand triumphant you must serve\r\nno master other than your own ambition.
You carried me through life,\r\nThe least I can do is carry you through death.
A heart can be stabbed by thoughts, \r\nIf your mind is sharp enough.
\"There is something incredibly satisfying about impaling test\r\nsubjects with Ethereal Knives. Perhaps it is the sound -\r\nthe spell, the screams, or both.\"  - Researcher Olesya

Whispers from a world apart
Speak my name beyond the tomb;
Bound within the Maelstr√∂m's heart,
Will they grant me strength or doom?
\"...The discomfort shown by the others is amusing, but none\r\ncan deny that my work has made quite the splash...\"\r\n- Maligaro's Journal

Existence is infinite
A weave of the living and dead
Beyond the understanding
Of the many mortal threads

Fire dances with those who doubt
Licks the skin and flesh from the fearful
Where there is no fear
There is no flame

For his sins he was hunted in his sleep,
judgement wrought of twisted nightmare.
The Coward bound his dreams to stone, awaiting
another to walk the path of true atonement.
Left in her tomb by the lynch mob, \r\nthe flame inside still blazed bright after her death, \r\nand so did hers.

"The Vaal were even more steeped in gem culture than 
our Emperor and his 'Gemlings'. It's an obsession 
as old as civilisation itself."
- Icius Perandus
\"A communion... but with what? By all accounts, \r\nit wasn't God that the Vaal were trying to reach.\"\r\n- Icius Perandus

"A waking Nightmare. 
Madness of the mind? 
Or madness of the flesh?"
- Icius Perandus

"Siosa, your Slavery will cause them to overlook you. 
Your Karui Way will guide you. 
Your Humanity will shame us all."
- Icius Perandus

Curious, she shook it then,
And tiny screams emerged.
Curiouser, she shook again,
And an eerie silence purred.
There was no hero made out of Starkonja's death,\r\nbut merely a long sleep made eternal.

"Man is blinded by the mud of his corporeal self. Only
through the transformation of the material into the
spiritual can we hope to taste the full body of life."
- Malachai the Soulless
As succulent as blood, as sweet as power.
A sigil of thaumaturgy graven in granite.
\"For the life of the flesh will always be in the blood.\"\r\n- Atalui, Vaal Priestess
The faithful may continue to serve, even after death.
Nature respects the strong\r\nAnd paints the snow red\r\nWith the blood of the weak
\"Test subject walked right through the poison gas defenses, and attempts to slow her\r\nfailed. Suppression troop six, the 'Furious Flagellants,' have been sent to intervene.\"
My bearer shall be guarded by flame,\r\nfor I am the phoenix, forever radiant in glory.

The night of a thousand ribbons
To remember the day of a thousand flames
When Sarn burned
And was born again
Forget your kite shield. Just put the biggest man\r\n in the field between you and the archers.
\"They say that you should take life's troubles in your stride.\r\nSome men have a longer stride than others.\"\r\n- Gaius Sentari

"Sirrius flew on wings of light, faster than wind, faster
than thought. But try as he might to outrun the darkness,
it was there, at every turn, waiting for him."
- Azmerian legend

Forged to rule the waves and tide
Destined to serve the monkey's paw
Strong as a tower of iron
Deft as the needle doubt
When Solaris closes her burning eye\r\nAt the end of time,\r\nthe world will perish in ice.
The greatest mistakes cause suffering \r\nlong after they have been made
One warrior, any armour.
Cool the head and cool the blade.
\"You shall hang, in blissful agony, on my every note.\"\r\n- Kalisa, Prima Donna of Sarn
\"Our superiors were getting anxious for results, and lowered security standards.\r\nA single attempt of a spell with this unexpected power destroyed an entire floor.\"
Death is beautiful. Let not the elements\r\nmar it with their clumsy ways.
Absolute corruption empowers absolutely.
The roar of the heavens\r\nStrikes more than fear\r\nInto the hearts of Man
The cards don't choose life and death\r\nThat's up to the player.

A lad with no fear of the pest 
Let rats fill his helmet in jest 
When they picked his skull clean
Where his head should have been
Was naught but a vermin-filled nest!
You are the powerless master of fire.
Many still hold the belief that the fossilised bones\r\nof Vaal sacrifices have magical properties.
When you have slain all of your enemies,\r\nwhat is left to fear?
\"While Prototype #3 does imbue its wearer with strength to match the original,\r\nthe first researcher to don it burst into flames when he walked into sunlight...\"
Many a collector of rarities discovered to his dismay\r\nthat the intelligent spirit in this sword\r\ndoes not like to share its master's attention

The ring I stole,
My finger they took,
A shrouded mind,
Cut their curses short,
As I drained their spirit
And stole their soul.
A blessing is often a curse.

Laughs of all the twisted
Echo through these halls of gold.
In this cold forgotten void
They wander, forever uncontrolled.
\"Suppression troop two, the 'Martyrs for Science,' were able to seal\r\nthe portals before Outpost Four was overrun. Only three men survived.\"
The second trial brought most to their knees.\r\nBut not you.
May you never hear it toll.
Desperate times demand desperate measures.
\"An absurdly vicious weapon in the hands of our test subjects. It seems to\r\nchannel the desperate will to live. Intriguing.\" \r\n- Researcher Olesya
It's cold and dark where the leviathan sleeps.\r\nColder and darker than death.\r\n- Old Sailor's saying
\"When the hyena howls thrice\r\ndeath is sure to follow.\"\r\n-Maraketh Wisdom
Gentle anger, raging calm.

The world is but a piece of parchment, blank and symmetric. 
We label each side: one Good, one Evil; one Black, one White. 
The divine truth, however, is that both are one and the same. 
-Jaetai, Vaal Advisor
\"A rare unequivocal success, Prototype #11 causes wounds to heal so quickly\r\nthe type Delta test subject actually survived the entire testing regimen.\"

By its light, Lori led her young charges to safety 
and bound up their wounds. 
Her sword arm was iron, yet her heart gentle 
and proof against hate.
\"What lies beneath your feet?!\"\r\n\"Sacred ground, watered with tears of blood!\"

When dead men rise and darkness falls
Only faith can be your walls
Walls of Light, not of brick
Twice as strong and twice as thick
. . . and the Light faded and hope waned\r\nZahndethus cast aside his faith\r\nand embraced the darkness.
\"The trick is to give nothingness,\r\nand to receive everything in return.\"\r\n- Inquisitor Maligaro
Though the Vaal revered peace, it would have \r\nbeen suicide for any culture to rouse them to war.\r\n- Icius Perandus, Scholar to the Empire.
RISE, SISTER!
The Treasures of the Tides wait\r\nin agony at the End of the World.
Flavour Text goes HERE
Flavourful flavour text is flavourful.
The portrait reflected his pain,\r\na pain that she could never see.
\"Here the soil is more deadly than any swing of the axe.\"\r\n- Oba of the Karui, Conqueror of Corruption.
It is too easy for the soul to escape from an open heart.
\"Nothing feels so smooth in the hand as Prototype #66.\r\nResults like these may justify everything we do here.\"

They flew, and leapt, and clambered over,
They crawled, and swam, and slithered under.
Still its ancient secrets await unclaimed
And of this hidden temple, only legends remain.
For this beauty,\r\nbeauty without strength,\r\nchokes out life.
\"A bit short in the arm, are you? \r\nThen you'll be short of a head soon enough.\"\r\n- Daresso the Daring
\"We are the soldiers of Faith, armoured in devotion.\r\nLet the sinners come, for we - the Pure - shall endure!\"\r\n- Voll of Thebrus, at the Battle of the Bridge
\"Grind your words into sharp thoughts.\r\nGrind your thoughts into the sharpest of deeds.\"\r\n- Victario, the People's Poet
God blesses those who bless themselves.
To truly appreciate life you must be there when it ends

"Shavronne held Sanity in her right
hand and Revelation in her left.
Brutus chose the left hand."
- Kadavrus, Surgeon to the Umbra
As long as the soul is unfettered, so is the body.
Flavourful flavour text is flavourful.

"Sharks thrash and swirl 
To the pounding drum of their frenzied hearts
As they dance in the waters red."
-Lavianga, Guardian of the Karui Way
Command like a king and nothing will stand in your way.
\"Prototype #599 offers an incredible defensive power, but at a cost.\r\nWhat underlying physics are at play here, I wonder?\"

Her purpose seems done; the oath is fulfilled.
Rust dulls her smirk with the last demon killed.
The embers grow dim and yet hope burns her lips:
"An old flame renewed can define our eclipse!"
Forge your Perseverance on the Anvil of Faith.
With death as my ally, all the world is within my grasp.
\"Our warehouses are bursting. Our vaults are full.\r\nBut our minds are still hungry.\"\r\n- Medici Perandus, Prefect to the Treasury
Let winter come. It will only make my fire burn brighter.

Knowledge is fermented in pain and loss
Distilled with reflection
To quench the thirst of those
who dream of enlightenment

Turning, gazing, blinking,
behold the eyes of void.
Burning, razing, drinking,
your mind is destroyed.

Shedding away her regal past, 
she forged a new destiny. 
Sacrificing the ephemeral joys of man, 
she embraced the eternal grasp of nature. 
Seizing her one true wish, 
she found peace at last.
Victory is on the march and nothing can stop it.
Those who burn for victory burn for eternity.
It hunts; as silent as falling snow, as deadly as the tempest.
\"Beware. Prototype #91 is haunted by a strange miasma,\r\nan odour of evil. Nothing can shield the senses.\" \r\n- Researcher Arn
Tears of blood, aching heart,\r\nMy dear Isildria must depart.
Fire and Anarchy are the most reliable agents of change.
\"The remarkable imbalance of Prototype #848 leads to uncommon\r\npower or speed when striking.\"
There is no safer place\r\nThan the Belly of the Beast
For none of us are as cruel as all of us.
\"Prototype #412 seems to bear much in\r\ncommon with Thought Extractor technology.\"
Where top is bottom and weak is strong.
\"Death can be outrun with these, but beware!\r\nIn running from death, you may forget to live.\"\r\n- Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Item 202
\"A lick of shadow may ease \r\nthe petty frictions of one's life.\"\r\n- Inquisitor Maligaro
\"Bored gods won't give you any favours.\"\r\n- Maraketh proverb
Bargg Wurmkin once severed the heads \r\nof seven men in a single cleave.
\"The finest prosperity grows from the direst\r\ncarnage. Such is the nature of progress.\"\r\n- Doryani of the Vaal
Heavy as guilt.\r\nBeautiful as temptation.\r\nPainful as betrayal.
Maligaro considered his work an Art, \r\nand his subjects his canvas.

A fang of hellfire, chip of frost,
Lightning flickers, blade embossed.
With dagger clenched, into the fray!
Or draw it out, and cast away.
Galla had an answer to everything.
\"We Ezomytes made promises that this \r\nEternal God would have us break.\" \r\n- Thane Rigwald

Beneath the blue,
The stillness permits
The drowned dead
To regret their choices.
The eldritch storm descended upon us, and bruised lightning\r\nrained down. Metal withered and flesh melted before its\r\narcane power. There was no escape, no shelter. Only despair.
Doedre Darktongue knew the Way of the Thaumaturge.\r\nIn order to receive, one must give... without hesitation.
\"Marylene stroked the medallion at her breast \r\nbefore every duel and every cast of the die.\" \r\n- Victario, the People's Poet
\"When one stares into the depth of the flavour text\r\nfile, one will gain no knowledge, only an addiction\r\nto speculation.\" - Maligaro, Grand Trolllord
\"I carry neither food nor drink. I rely on the charity\r\nof my fellow wayfarers. Dead men are generous men.\"\r\n- Taruk of the Wildmen
Give yourself to the flames and your name\r\nwill burn in the minds of men forever.
\"Ice and flame antagonized in the essence of a prototype.\r\nWhat once burned now chills the soul.\" \r\n- Researcher Arn
Tread lightly, lest their vigil find you.\r\nSpeak softly, lest their reason fend you.\r\nCut gently, lest their spirit haunt you.

"A raging Solaris seared and contorted the orb's surface. 
A despairing Lunaris filled the scars with her tears. 
Yet Viridi remained, trapped within, forever more."
 - Azmerian Creation Myth

"When your back is against the wall,
And your opponent is bleeding you dry,
There is only one appropriate response:
Unbridled, overwhelming violence."
- Daresso, the Sword King
\"Let the evil ones deliver their fiery darts.\r\nThis time I've put my faith in steel.\"\r\n - Commander Santoni of the Damned Brotherhood

Ming slew Tranquillity
Took Chaos for his wife
And on Her immortal finger
He placed his Heart
\"There's nothing like imminent death\r\nto galvanize one's purpose in life.\"\r\n- Malachai the Soulless.

The Empress gave Romira two sons
Born of his brother's seed
Romira threw her a banquet
A perfidious meal indeed.

Born of love, forged in blood
He burned as a torch in the blackest night
She shone as ice in the winter sun
Proudly, fiercely
At their mother's side, forever.
The sun's fury, trapped\r\nin pillars of blazing light,\r\nExplodes from its cage.
Anticipation, preparation, exhilaration, celebration.

"From Frost's ice-bound pass
Berek taunted and jeered
Until furious Flame scaled the mountain
Berek escaped through the thaw
And Frost's tortured moans."
- Berek and the Untamed

"Berek hid from Storm's lightning wrath
In the embrace of oblivious Frost
Repelled by ice, blinded by blizzards
Storm raged in vain
While Berek slept."
- Berek and the Untamed

"With Flame licking at his heels
Berek berated the clouds
Until vengeful Storm spewed forth his rains
And Berek held on tight
As Fire screamed and steamed
And fled."
- Berek and the Untamed

"Moon after moon did Berek make fools
Of the great and Untamed Three
Until malice for a Brother
Slew the hatred of the Other
And Berek did hunt
Alone and free."
- Berek and the Untamed

"Kaom fought and killed for his people.
Kaom bled for his people.
And so the people gave, the people bled,
So their King might go on."
- Lavianga, Advisor to Kaom
\"When the Ancestors fill your cup,\r\nIt is only good manners to drink your fill.\"\r\n- Lavianga, Advisor to Kaom
\"An intriguing paradox.\"

"It is the Gull that delivers Man unto Ancestor.
The consumer of our flesh. The seeder of our
souls unto the earth. We give the Gull his life.
The Gull gives us our Way."
- Lavianga, Advisor to Kaom

"A man's soul rules from a cavern of bone, learns and
judges through flesh-born windows. The heart is meat.
The head is where the Man is."
- Lavianga, Advisor to Kaom
\"A type Delta test subject escaped with Prototype #18. He was last seen\r\nten times the height of a man and crashing straight through walls.\"

you know death will follow soon.

Whiff of cold, tiny spark, faintest flicker in the dark.
Embers swirl, ice takes form, sky exposed - Death's perfect storm.
Frost and thunder, flames shine bright, ruin walks the land tonight.
By your hand they dance and bend, wield them and brook no end.
To discover how cruel nature can be,\r\nyou need only shake the wrong branch.
Some things must die so that others can live.

"He does not love. He does not feel regret or remorse.
He does not think about consequences, only possibilities.
If that does not describe a monster, tell me: what does?"
- Archbishop Geofri
Ask any tracker and they'll tell you:\r\nthe most dangerous animals\r\nare the ones who don't bother to hide.
\"Decomposition takes hold too quickly!\r\nNo, if we are to keep the specimen in perfect shape,\r\nwe must begin the process before expiry.\"

"Nothing is more natural than competition.
One feasts, another starves.
One blossoms, another withers.
And one cannot catch the golden sunlight
without casting a bitter shadow."
- Cadiro Perandus
\"There seems to be some innate relationship between the forces of\r\nchaos and cold. Perhaps we should consult an occultist.\"
Though the path we walk is the same,\r\neach journey is different.
\"Prototype #56 was deemed safe, but judging by Administrator Qotra's new hustle\r\nand improved ability to micromanage us, I'm not so sure.\" \r\n- Researcher Graven
You do not cease to be when you die\r\nany more than the caterpillar ceases to be when it cocoons.\r\nCome, let me show you.
\"Prototype #73 is a near perfect opposite of the original. Perhaps our failures\r\nare due to some unknown polarity we have yet to discover.\"

The impediments of flesh are weak.
The air we breathe knows no such boundaries.
I exhale, and you inhale,
and inexorably we inch towards oneness.

Feed a beast and it will not hunt.
Protect it and it will not fight.
Ferocity must be learned, not taught.
It is suffering that forges the greatest warriors.

He took me by my hand, promised me power beyond compare.
But I did not do it for power.
I did it for love.
And I'd do it again in an instant.
What man does not wish for immortality?
Whispered memory,\r\nA shimmer in the darkness.\r\nForgotten no more.
Though flesh may decay, and bones turn to dust, the spirit fades not.\r\nFloundering eternal in pools of tranquil dark.

Ambition followed progress,
Vanity followed passion,
Hubris followed intellect...
And silence followed all.
The craftsman rots.\r\nHis tools rust.\r\nBut his legacy cuts through the ages.
The words of a man, delicate like life, pass on feebly into forgotten verse,\r\nbut his creations... his craft shall be championed agelessly.
Time is a river, forking forever into infinite unknowns.\r\nNothing is ever truly gone.\r\nIt is merely taking a different route to the sea.
All creatures have the potential for greatness\r\nor unequivocal failure.
Vaal bloodpriests were among the earliest intellectuals on record. \r\nIt was they who found that a newly freed soul would \r\ndesperately cling to any other source of life.
\"Curious. The test spike penetrated the subject's flesh, but the chest wound\r\nwas not as deep as expected. There is something here...\"
Silent, silent night,\r\nQuench the holy light.
Eternal soldiers fight for glory or death.\r\nThe Solaris Vanguard know only glory.
The mind had much to endure before the advent of thaumaturgy.
Wealth can, in fact, buy happiness.
'Lightning never strikes the same place twice'\r\nis really just wishful thinking.
In the prison of all sins, will you grasp godhood or sorrow? Only hope lies under the shadows.
In combat, a warrior must first be resourceful,\r\nand second, decisive.
<size:31>{There is no mistake so great that it cannot be undone.}
If you wish to rush into strange places, be prepared to face strange things.
Some powers are far too great even for the\r\ngods of old.
Lethal, untouchable, keen, aflame. Just what I was looking for.
<size:30>{Many strive for greatness,\r\nbut it is challenge, unforseen,\r\nthat forges heroes.}
He shattered Her smile\r\nScattered the fragments like ash\r\nAll she did was laugh
A lust for souls. The urge to kill just to satisfy its thirst. An unbearable burden that would make even the purest heart blacken over time.
Our world, dangerous as it is, is far safer than what lies just beyond our sight.

<size:24>{Do the simple words used 
alone cause men to cheer? 
One hundred others might 
just as soon make a jeer. 
Perchance it was the turn 
of the tone in this bit. 
See how their hearts shone once, 
by my song, they were lit.}
Some things should not be used. Some power is too great a risk.
Ever get the feeling you're being watched...?

<size:29>{A dark note drips 
from the dreamer's lips, 
A honeyed melody. 
We stand, we fall 
on his beck and call, 
for in his dream we're free.}
Its body knows no limits. Its appetite knows no bounds.
Beware the combatant who shows no confidence, yet still enters the ring, for they are surely hiding something.
When the darkness weighs upon you, grow light from within.
As countless fractures weaken the divide, nightmares seep through from the other side.

<size:27>{A wanderer in the wild strives 
Against countless foes he survives 
A fool pursues a quest contrived 
By the gift of the witch, alive.}
The threads of fate are the strongest ties.
The jeweller's true talent is the capacity to see a jewel's beauty before they draw it out.
A dream from which you cannot awake is nothing other than a nightmare.
In a world filled with chaos, he could always seek comfort in the hands of his master.
Fall into endless night; a voyage into an ocean of oblivion.
<size:29>{\"Fate was always my nemesis... \r\nBut it didn't stop me then, and it won't stop me now.\"\r\n- Kjetilbrann, The Undaunted}
Lucian lost himself in ancient scrolls and found in those scrolls a love whose power bridged a millennium.

<size:26>{Many were slain by the sword king 
Their blood decorating his ring 
Those who retreated were slaughtered 
Those who fought bravely were honoured}

<size:28>{I gave my mind without a fight, 
The twelfth hour I lost control. 
The day is gone but there is light, 
eyes that glow like red-hot coal.}
Stare into its depths too long, and you may lose yourself entirely.
There are countless worlds, but only those with limitless potential will be able to achieve perfection.
All dreams vanish when the dreamers wake.

<size:29>{Shrieking souls locked away 
Hate splits frozen cells asunder 
The knot of corruption
undone at last}
At night, when the seas are calm, and the skies dark, he can see it. The formless fiend that took his eye, and fractured his mind.
Though the years weakened his mind, his body remained deadly as ever.
A ruler is only as powerful as he is wealthy. \r\nControl the coin, control the empire.
To create something truly spectacular, you must risk total failure.

<size:29>{A mind as quick as lightning, 
fists as hard as stone, 
a heart that burns with fury, 
and eyes that chill to the bone.}
The village elders had a curious rule: If you hear three voices scream for aid, flee as fast as you can.
The academic route to knowledge is wide and well-trodden; but it is the untaught one who scales the mountain.
To know the monster, you must become the monster.
His brother would not atone, so he took his brother's life, and with it, his sins.
Though the path to divinity is fraught with peril, hope may bloom from within.
Gaze towards the stars, but beware what gazes back.
Her beauty did not fade \r\nher humanity did not survive.
To protect her mansion, she would cut a deal with anyone. Anything. \r\n\r\nSomething answered.

<size:28>{Wreathed in the skin and bones
of the beasts she slew, 
her gift came from what she lost: 
her humanity.}
The day is dying, the night is born, the air grows cool, the sky is torn.
Nothing can be heard above the din or seen amongst the turmoil. The senses are shattered. All is left to fate.
For some, the price of power is never too great.
The Poet's blood is the Empire's ink.
We tried to tell him to get his head checked.
Perfection is the standard, excellence will be handled on a case by case basis.
\"The process of eternal youth is a give and take. You give them death and take their youth.\"\r\n- Zerphi of the Vaal
All that is flawed is worthless. The slightest error, and this might as well be trash.

<<hbgi04>><<HBG04>><<HBGAt>><<HBG03>><<HBGAs>><<HBG01>><<HBGAy>><<HBG01>><<HBGBa>>

Fear the man who lusts for power, for he will do anything to get it.
Some gifts are obligations while others are simply opportunities.
Oh the places you will go, the sights you will see, the things you will meet.
Discovery can lead to beauty, or it can lead to ruin.
Warriors of a distant land, you embark on a journey from which you may not return, but which we will be all the better for.

<size:28>{Charmed by beautiful stones 
Consumed with the 
pursuit of perfection 
Ever deeper into the waiting dark}
If enough people believe something to be true, whether or not it is becomes irrelevant.
Before gemlings, before thaumaturgy, a simple court magician could enthrall the masses.
<size:28>{\"You cannot portray the world using just one colour. Together, you and I, we will paint our world into perfection.\" \r\n- Kyra, renegade thaumaturgist}
\"Only a fool looks to the occult for power and expects to be spared from its wrath.\" \r\n- Voll, Emperor of Purity
\"Sometimes, the most beautiful treasures...are the ones you cannot have.\" \r\n- Beryl, Survivor from the Azurite Mines
<size:34>{He dispels dark realms\r\nuntil mortal sufferings\r\nyield to hopeful light.}
Though they were a pack of elite combatants, the Emperor's royal guards were not ready to face one of his notorious parties.
A life lost, A legacy born.

<size:28>{There's a place where up is down, 
where right is wrong, 
where pleasure is agony, 
and where the living wish only for death.}
We play at God with our necromancy, \r\nbut forces far more potent \r\nsleep within these stones.
\"I gave up my body for you. I gave up my name for you. And one day I shall give up my life for you.\"
<size:28>{A ravenous mind can readily take in ideas from any source. \r\nFortunately for the scholars, he has already learned about sustainability.}
<size:28>{A treasure worth killing for \r\nis a treasure worth dying for.}
Even the most learned man is a fool to his own fate.
Upon silent paws and masked by the reeds, \r\nFarrul's hunt begins as the light recedes.
<size:28>{\"The Seas Call, the Mad Answer\"}
\"When grasped in his hand, even an ordinary piece of wood can make the heavens tremble with fear.\"
No one ever truly understood what she meant when she said she wanted to raise a family.
<size:28>{You can't seek riches without getting your hands dirty.}
Sometimes you need to make your own luck.
Hear me, fish! I love and respect you, but before this day ends I will kill you dead.

<size:28>{Every skull was once a person. 
Though 'Who?' is rarely asked. 
Friends, who wear 
the crown of Nook, 
Never need to ask. 
They remember.}
You'll never know the things you miss if you keep your eyes closed
\"Forge me a carapace from their skin, imbued with their soul. Then feed their flesh to the hounds.\"
Try a thousand times, and eventually you'll have to give up.
<size:28>{\"For all your struggles, all your achievements, even for the greatest of us, a story is all that remains. Write it well.\" \r\n\r\n-Julius Perandus, Father of Chitus}
Greed is a hunger that only grows as you feed it

<size:24>{Dread and danger 
makes the air feel thin. 
Above, power slumbers, tempting fate. 
Greed and ambition 
draws countless in, 
For those who seek power 
can never wait.}
In the pursuit of power, as in that of wealth, anything goes.
Method transcends shape and size. Do something in parallel long enough, and you will always find \r\nanother way.
They stand among us, and within us.
The Lord of Chaos dreams as his Eye gazes, unblinking, at his prize. And soon, all shall tremble before his waking form.
A man who hears voices may not necessarily be crazy.
<size:28>{The hatungo know many answers to the same question, \r\nfor time itself is a tangled web.}
<size:28>{Souls along a conduit of blood, \r\nfrom one vessel to the next.}
Though the forces of nature are mighty and intimidating, it is their absence which should be feared.
In the pursuit of wealth, as in that of power, anything goes.
The howls and cackling could not mask the sadness.
The line between having not enough to do and too much to do is unusually fine.
Blessed is the blood of the beholden disciple. The earth is anointed by his step. The damnable are sanctified by his strike.
\"In the forest again... But at least I have these.\"
In fleeing reality, you step into the realm of madness.
\"The Karui was correct; there is virtue in honouring my ancestors.\"
They whose lives were given to clothe the Dark Dreamer... They were the lucky ones.
\"There are two ways to pay, Gold and Blood. I'll take my share in both.\"\r\n\r\n-Cameria the Coldblooded
Many sought the Goddess' blessing. Few survived the Labyrinth to receive it.
However vicious Rhoas might be, a dedicated angler may in time tame them.
The flesh is a prison, and we are finally free.
\"Set your life on fire. Seek those who fan your flames\"\r\n\r\n-Rumi of the Vaal
What was once a passing thought tickling the back of the mind is now a desperate, driving desire.
When you strive to write your name on the dense pages of History, someone else, inevitably, must be crossed out.
\"Our rulers are being ridiculous, and we are suffering.\"
Know thine enemy better than you know thyself.
Sometimes the best way to achieve greatness is to use a shortcut.
Trying to bring your vision to life is enough to drive you mad.
\"I'm going for a walk. I'll be back soon.\"\r\n\r\n - Blonca's last words
Born beneath silver light, bearing Lunaris' mark.\r\nConjuring all his might, the Prodigy turned light to dark.
Time dismantles all things eventually, but some wish to accelerate the process.

<size:30>{A King Loved By All,
A Shadow Awaiting Nightfall,
A Speaker Howling Away,
A Hunter Seeking Prey}
Only the feminine touch can save a man's soul from the clutches of The Wasteland.
Within years of knowledge, distilled by careful craftsmanship, lies great power.
The Golden Sekhema's words could solve many a feud. Just what form that solution took was another matter.
<size:30>{The artist is long dead,\r\nthe lyrics are long forgotten,\r\nyet the Song of War longs to be sung again}
Chasing purity in the rising light means facing the darkening edges of the spirit.
Where Decay festers, I shall expunge it, and leave in its place a shining monument.
It is a mortal man's folly to seek power beyond his comprehension.
She took all she had and turned it into something she was craving.
Savour these moments, for they may never return.
Some seek to change the world. Others change the world as a consequence of what they seek.
The mighty huntress always called for her share,\r\nBut what we shared was a lifelong bond.
\"This was the proudest moment of my life.\"\r\n\r\n\"... so far\"
<size:28>{I thought love stronger than all,\r\nbut time and isolation broke\r\nthat which madness could not.}
The pain you feel is of no consequence, it is evolution, to be made whole within something greater.
The Mists of Madness prey on those who harbour the deepest of fears.
<size:26>{The pale flame of his heart disappeared in his azure reflection.\r\nThe work of a life.\r\nAmbitious, and unfinished.}

<size:23>{Vintage or crafted, Glittering and shiny
Dusty or glittering, huge or tiny
Secured within a chest 
or unearthed from your mining
Find jewellery everywhere, 
no need for divining!
So why is it so hard 
to figure out which one to wear?
This one makes me stronger, 
but does it match my hair?}
<size:26>{\"Such dedication for so many years,\r\nall for a couple extra letters at the front of your name...\"}
<size:25>{Awoken virtuous slivers of the void,\r\ndefiled by the avaricious, \r\nseized by the tyrannical.}
Even though he found the stash just in time,\r\nHe would trade it all away and then some to have him back.
Mold the world with your bare hands. Be careful, for what is your doing might become your undoing.
They came from far and wide under a common banner.\r\nThey sought companionship and competition,\r\nbut found a treasure none had foreseen.
If you look hard enough for hidden meaning, you will find it.
A good spy doesn't forget she's gone undercover.
In the dead of night you may elude your shadows,\r\nbut they will always find you by dawn.

The world is ever-changing.
Once-lush woods now lost beneath shifting sands,
Great cities now drown beneath turbulent waters.
Adapt or perish.

<size:25>{They thought winter had come early,
that snow blanketed the land,
but in truth, all their chickens
had come home to roost.}

<size:28>{We live to dream of worlds we aren't in,
a false narrative that we use to fill our souls
with doubt;
The world is already beautiful,
there's no need to dream.}
Even the brightest eventually fade to darkness.
<size:26>{Some people act as beacons, illuminating the path for others. I was lucky to meet one such person.\r\n\r\n- Anton to Zhenya}

<size:24>{They would say that he was a dangerous man,
unbound by the sense of morality,
but what does this matter,
when his love for humanity is undeniable
and completion of his work would benefit everyone?}
With great power comes...\r\n\r\n...Even greater power.
Why settle when more is never enough.
\"I know one lady for whose sake I will rip out my heart\"\r\n\r\n- Derrok, the Dreamer
The suit I wear,\r\nIs heavy and bare.\r\nA canvas, it seems, breathing life into dreams.
I have a headache, can anyone find me a nurse?
<size:26>{The rain pelts down, Mud grasping at his feet, as thoughts of those in his care bolster his resolve.}

<size:24>{For the blessed bear in the cave,
A hundred days pass in silence and darkness,
until moon begins its fourth passage,
the bear sheds her beastly fur,
and is reborn, human and whole.}

<size:25>{Seeking shelter from the night,
in the warmth of the run-down inn,
erstwhile foes put aside the fight,
to bond over whiskey and gin.}

<size:29>{Come home to me, my sweet.
Oh, how long you've been!
Lie with me in the frozen dark.
I may yet find forgiveness
Now that fear has left you.}
No blade subdues vice;\r\nGuide offenders to virtue,\r\nUnveil their lost sight.
<size:25>{\"Glimmers of benevolence,\r\nShrouded a lacquered lust for power,\r\nYet still they followed his influence.\"}
Experience teaches us that the cold is not the same as the absence of warmth.
\"Man may shape the world, but these? These shape the man.\" -Inquisitor Maligaro
<size:27>{\"Be fast. That is all that matters.\"\r\n- Rita of the Asylum}
Dost thou lead my men to victory, my child?
They believed, falsely, that the strongest of generals could outlast eons of corruption.
One who is blinded by their past may only see a sliver of the present.
If time is the most valuable currency, how do you make more of it?
\"The house always wins... except when I do.\"
<size:25>{Cede all power and wealth to me and serve me in perpetuity.\r\nA minor inconvenience I assure you.}

<size:24>{Plenty enter, dreaming of treasure
Twenty bled, slain as they fled
Shadows loom, half left doomed
The blind cries, five lost eyes
Careless twins, a lich's new prize
One as a decoy, none pass the king
Gehennix feeds only on whispers}
Every obsession began with a single, innocent taste.
\"Bino's brief career as a chef at Axiom saved the executioner a lot of work.\"
He appeared before the Light Eater, and at once knew his soul was damned.
The harvest ended, the floods began.
The swarm began with just a couple of children. Now, it is her entire existence.
<size:26>{The strange voice showed Aul a future where his legacy was forgotten, where new cultures broke themselves upon Aul's ruined world.}

<size:28>{Through the eyes of a person, 
you can see their soul
Through the eyes of a jewel, 
you can see the universe}
They said they were here to protect us.
While the Labyrinth traps have claimed countless adventurers, they were not designed with felines in mind.
\"Oh no, I couldn't possibly afford this fine artefact. I'm... just looking.\"
Without the ability to weep, the heart hardens against both the pure and the corrupt.
<size:28>{I never truly understood the depths of my insanity,\r\nuntil I realized the voices beckoning me towards the abyss,\r\nwere none other than my own.}
The most pathetic person in the world is someone who has sight, but no vision.
\"It's not Karui, Azmeri or even Vaal in origin,\r\nbut one thing is certain. It is very, very old.\"\r\n- Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Item 46

The summer sun dries the soil and burns the leaves.
The autumn rain extinguishes the flames.
The spring bloom shades the wet earth.
Nature is an eternal tug of war.

From Weylam to Meredith:\r\nI shall love thee as I love the sea.
To the wily Kishara's eye, a star brighter than the sun.
\"The cool blanket of shadows preserves our treasures.\"\r\n - Inquisitor Maligaro
\"Certain maps can only be rendered in the most vivid of viscera.\"\r\n - Inquisitor Maligaro
\"A boy becomes a man when he has faced the animal\r\nin his heart and wet the forest floor with its blood.\"\r\n - Azmeri Proverb
\"The spider is not defined by how\r\nit lives, but by how it kills.\"\r\n - Inquisitor Maligaro
In all things living, the light burns bright.
A passionate fire that consumes the heart.
The Spirit, it radiates not from above.
It is the warmth that draws you ever inward.
Where rest the truest colours of life.
Gold of the organ. Green of the throat. Red of the vein.
The myriad wet rainbow of the Spirit's domain.
\"Weakness must be purged lest it\r\npoison the blood of all Karui.\"\r\n - Prayer to Tukohama
\"A stranger's kiss on a moonlit night.\r\nDost thou believe in love at first sight?\"
\"May the lubbers feel fear in their\r\nnethers, and may our blades follow.\"\r\n - Rot-tooth's Rallying Cry
\"We shall peer at these cosmic wonderments as they\r\nwake and writhe within that deep and nameless dark.\"\r\n - Vilenta, 'Miasmeter: A Thesis'
Eyes blazing with holy flame, the Pilgrim saw\r\na great palace descend from the burgeoning sky,\r\nits gates barred against the unfaithful.
Wrought from blood and gold, Innocence fashioned a weapon of tempered purity,\r\ncapable of banishing darkness, and bringing order to the chaos in men's hearts.

"The sun is a devoted mother. She casts her golden blessings on
the crops of the pious and makes barren the fields of heresy.
Sunlight is belief. Sunlight is life."
 - The Solar Verses

"Moonlight is a wise mother. The moon which bathes us in soft,
cooling light, does so with the intent of illuminating our paths.
Moonlight is wisdom. Moonlight is life."
 - The Lunar Verses
\"The amulet, it... whispers to me. Horrible things...\"
And mounting her mighty Roc, Garukhan, holy queen of the sky,\r\ndescended upon her enemies and their armies of darkness.
This gem is only temporary, and only for the tutorial.
Power is a curious thing. \r\nIt can be contained, hidden, locked away, \r\nand yet it always breaks free.
\"And how shall we know a sekhema worthy of rule? \r\nBy the anointing of the Great Roc, under whose wings we grow and soar.\"\r\n - Maraketh Coronation Ritual

Garukhan sought madness and knowledge amongst the billowing clouds of a \r\nblackened sky. A vulture of pride, she would not be refused, and so the\r\nstratosphere divulged unto her eldritch secrets of its tumultuous past.
\"Blow it all down! The emperor must have his gems, no matter the cost!\"

Nobility once thought to capture the Basilisks and keep them as exotic pets.\r\nThis only served to fatten the vileness of their hearts, and with a hateful\r\nacid that festered inside, the creatures became soured to their very bones.

The King looked upon images swirling atop the ancient stone dial.
"You look peaceful" he told his bride-to-be, "So peaceful, asleep in our wedding bed."
But in phantasm, she did not slumber, and what he saw was not a place for dreams,
rather, a wooden box... about to be closed and lowered into earthy depths.
 - Maraketh Legend

"One should not entice the storm; one cannot invite the storm, or give warrant
to its tyrant-soul. We survive only by appeasing the storm, with gifts and
offerings of adoration. We hope that, in its mercy, it shall pass us by."
- Tempestology of the Maraketh, Repudion IV
Famous for her many lovers, those that did not\r\ncome willing to Atziri, came by liquid persuasion.
\"T'gnagn iia y r'ngusla ph'tu Tsoatha nga mekghul'an.\"\r\n - Indecipherable verse
\"Worry not for the heathens. They are devoid of soul.\r\nMade vessels of wrath, they are damned by holy design.\"\r\n- High Templar Avarius
In the end, time comes for all of us.\r\nFor some, it comes much sooner.
\"Would you leave an orchard of apples to rot unharvested?\r\nA cemetery is no different.\" \r\n-Kadavrus, Surgeon to the Umbra
Like lightning, the Ezomyte cavalry need never strike twice.
The monstrous men of yore used bows too,\r\ntheirs were just bigger.
Countless men proclaimed themselves the masters of death,\r\nand each one succumbed to it.

"Creation is the act of making the intangible tangible.
To work backwards, to make the tangible intangible,
is to step into the mind of a god."
- Doryani, Queen's Thaumaturgist
