<<HBGAa>><<HBG01>><<HBGAf>><<HBG02>><<HBGAm>><<HBG03>><<HBGAo>>\r\n<<HBG02>><<HBGAt>><<HBG03>><<HBGAy>>

Though his mind decayed with each passing wave,
the Brine King stood steadfast in his hatred,
and wore it like a shell, protecting himself 
from his failure to sire a worthy heir.

The fish-wives of Tsoatha rejoiced loudly as
the Brine King descended into the great abyss,
making merry while his blasphemous offspring
slithered 'neath the icy waters...

Slumbering in the breach between worlds,
the Brine King dreamt of a day he would rise,
in triumph from the shivering depths and take
back the Kingdom he once so ruthlessly culled.

There is a story held by the ancient Vaal, in which the
beautiful seductress Arakaali strode through towns, stealing
the hearts of men, and turning to ash their lovers' desires.
- "Legends of the Vaal" by Eramir, Scholar at Theopolis

When the cold was at its strongest, Arakaali came,
and like a farmer leading cattle to the slaughter,
she drove her victims into the outer darkness.
- "Legends of the Vaal" by Eramir, Scholar at Theopolis

Records of Arakaali's violent reign suggest she kept her citizens
sedated with 'juices of lust' and venoms of the spider. Perhaps her
guise of seductress was in fact her way of farming those 'juices'.
- "Legends of the Vaal" by Eramir, Scholar at Theopolis
The mud is cracked and dry. The fields now burn beneath the blistering sun.\r\nEven our children are dying in the streets! We've angered Solaris and so\r\nwe pay tribute to appease her fiery heart...

When Solaris is angered, there must always be sacrifice. Our women\r\nhave taken to mourning, they drag themselves through ash and glass,\r\nnot wanting to give up our youth to the all-consuming flame.

To take from the sun is to invite her wrath, and we've more than warranted her curse.\r\nThe granaries were vacant, so we lessened our tribute to the sun thinking it would\r\nsave our children, but they will die now regardless.

Once beneath a moonlit sky, Lunaris bathed her child in the ocean's tide.\r\nThough the waters were frigid with icy death, the boy was sick and\r\ncouldn't be healthy until he was silent, clean and still...

And so it was, that Lunaris, in her compulsion to nurture and protect,\r\nkilled her son beneath the light of a waning moon. She stood silent, in\r\ntrial before her tribe, as her fiery sister fought in vain to defend her...

But Lunaris refused to admit any wrongdoing. She'd saved her child, had she not?\r\nHe was safe now, buried beneath the dirt. Conviction gnarled around her fragile mind,\r\nand in her pride she rose to seat a deathless throne.

When the demon Goat plays his flute,
And cloven hooves clip-clop your path,
Pray the gods will hold you mute,
And bless the fire on your hearth.

The earth shakes, moon eclipses black.
Graveyards quake, crops turn to ash,
as the grieving mother weeps.
Oceans boil and wind ravages home. 
We feel famine inside our bones,
as the grieving mother, Gruthkul weeps.

In nature, there are many feelings exclusive only to man. But terror is not one.
Terror flourishes in our world, transcending all things. It is the bedrock on
which our great cosmos is formed. I am Yugul and I deign to understand this
mystery, to explore its depths and unlock its secrets...
\"So it's true.\" Shakari thought, as she took her final breath.\r\n\"My father, Sin, wishes me dead. And he has sent his rabid dog to do it...\"

Tukohama stood in the door, blocking the sunlight
from Hikatomanga and his family. The Father of War's
retribution was inevitable, for it is known - man
cannot cheat the gods without consequence...
\"Lock the gates and build the walls!\" came the rallying cry,\r\n\"Let those of Ralakesh take care of those of Ralakesh!\"\r\n- The God Behind The Wall

Garukhan wished once more for the skies. If she were to die,
she wanted it to be up there in the clouds. This world had never
been her home. She required greater things. She required adventure.
But die she would, here in the dirt...

Ryslatha was flushed with pride as she watched her mindless spawn\r\nmature. Sharpening their mandibles, her children slithered from the hive,\r\neager to devour all the creatures that frequented the ancient woods.
In the shadow of war,\r\nall are eclipsed.
We are ever the makers of our own undoing.
Man creates where nature cannot.
\"Whatever these maps are, it is clear they are dangerous. Send in only\r\ntest subjects, no guards or researchers.\" \r\n- Administrator Qotra
For the immortal, what is the difference\r\nbetween an age and an instant?
Be careful where you put your finger.
In every piece of prose, lies a tiny spark of magic.

In the years that followed the twisted sky,
cold winds cloaked Wraeclast in snow.
The pure-white blanket masked a black heart
that lay dormant deep beneath the earth.
The skilled know how to learn.\r\nThe talented know who to learn from.
\"Twelve test subjects were expended in the production of Prototype #800.\r\nWas it worth the expense? Only time will tell.\"

"Every day we choose safety or knowledge. 
Live and stagnate, or risk death for truth.
I would rather see the end of the Vaal
than help it tread water." 
- Doryani, Queen's Thaumaturgist
\"What cruelty it is, that to be judged a success,\r\nsuch great work must go uncredited.\" \r\n- Coralito, Brotherhood of Silence
Your memories are a bridge to the past.\r\nLet no one cross.
One's burden is another's gift.
Dance like dust on the desert wind.
The Maraketh fear very little, \r\nbut they dare not whisper the name\r\nof the demon that flies on Winter's gales.

Through droughts, fires, floods and frost,
the ancient giants stand resolute,
while deep in the rich, dark earth,
their grasp stretches ever farther.
Let the unrepentant be dragged ever downwards by the weight of their sins.
Enough mice can kill a wolf.
Hurt as you would be hurt.
Even the dead serve the Lightless.
\"Ever watched a man crush another man's skull?\r\nHard to feel hope after that.\"
Hold in your hand the darkness\r\nand never will the light blind you.
The eyes of the living hold a glimmer of hope.\r\nDon't waste it.
Look to the darkness for nourishment and you will never go hungry.
\"Eyes of black, three by three, staring ever darker into me...\"\r\n- Researcher Arn

Land and sea did not dissuade,
nor did the Kelpie's maw;
the wild beast crossed half the world
to sate his hungry claw.

Candles with the brightest light
Bring life to death and day to night.
But lovely as the glow may seem,
Their light is fleeting, as a dream...

As she was sentenced to death, Doedre was silent.
As she was tied to the stake, Doedre was silent.
As the flames licked away her life, Doedre was silent.
But Wraeclast had not heard the last of her.
\"The Council have a great many secrets.\r\nSome are better kept that way, Cospri.\"\r\n- Mauritius, the Iron Heart
Though its body was locked in stone,\r\nits essence wandered the infinite,\r\nlearning, and preparing.
With the patience of a prowling lion,\r\nthe Shade watched the Scholar.
One by one, they stood their ground against a creature \r\nthey had no hope of understanding, let alone defeating,\r\nand one by one, they became a part of it.
Reaching nature's limits, \r\nmany sought power in the unnatural.
They hoped that, trapped in its prison,\r\nthe creature would age and perish.\r\nBut time would not touch the fiend.

Their last thoughts were not of their friends,
or their families, or their homes.
Their last thoughts were untethered from reality,
and bathed in fear and ferocity.
All at once, a calmness would encompass them,\r\nand all at once, it would be torn away,\r\nunveiling forms no sound mind could grasp.
Men always fell for her honeyed eyes,\r\nand broke when they hit the ground.

Lunaris crossed silently, shining and full, 
Softly night left her, alone and forlorn.
Solaris rose to meet her, feeling her pull.
'Neath the midday sun, the night was reborn.
When the world spins out of control,\r\nthe safest place to be is in the centre.
Through countless seasons they stand, stoic,\r\nEach season leaving its mark; \r\na memory written in fibrous flesh.
By wind and wing they are carried,\r\nTheir fates not theirs to control,\r\nYet the fates of others dragged in their wake.

Lava bled from the earth and,
after a time, cooled and hardened.
The world protecting its beating heart 
with a thick, black scab.
Darkness never stops feeding.

"Your name is Demon Slayer? Really? Good name for rotgut, that."
She said: I prefer "The Goddess Of Swords". Much more dignified. And accurate.
"Demon Slayer The Cheap And Nasty it is then. Burns going down, burns coming up?"
She said: Every single time, Charan. And still...you'll bathe me, and you'll drink my love. Until you can't.

"...A golden machine was found broken in the ruins of Wraeclast. 
Believing it to contain some dark infernal secret, 
High Templar Venarius asked that I restore it 
and weaponize whatever powers it might contain..."

"...Though the device seemed to be mostly functioning, 
something important appeared to be missing...
...I worked tirelessly in search of answers, until finally, 
at the base of that cruel device, I fell into a deep, deep sleep..."

"...I awoke in the most beautiful of places, and as I wandered this strange new land, 
I felt a growing sense of realization that I was not alone. 
A Shade, a whisper of embodied smoke, spoke to me through thoughts and pictures.
I found myself enthusiastically volunteering information in detail of Oriath..."

"...The Shade knew of the device - a doorway between my world
and the dreamlands. It offered to help me rebuild the missing part, 
to create a conduit between this beautiful land and Oriath. 
All that the Shade asked of me was to return the favour..."

"...Every night, I found myself asleep at the foot of the strange device, 
awoken to the reality of another world within my own.
The Shade taught me how to shape and build things from my imagination,
how to transport such phantasmagorical treasures back into the world of man..."

"...The missing part of the great device had finally been formed.
The Shade requested its one favour. I was shown images of the past,
the Shade as King of the dreamlands, the hateful Watchers of Decay...
It led me deep into a cave, to a statue pierced by a sword..."

"Pull the blade from my chest. Free me!" the Shade imposed.
But doubt entered my mind, and the Shade flew into a fury!
I felt my mind torn asunder as images of murder and mutilation were forced upon me. 
I fled in a panic, cursing myself for ever trusting such a strange creature so blindly..."

"...Months have now passed since the Shade revealed its true nature.
Each morning, I lock myself inside my study, searching for some knowledge 
that might save us. I have found at last, some information on the Watchers of Decay. 
The truth is so unutterable that I hesitate, even now, to write it down..."

"...They called it the Elder. A creature of malignant madness... it cannot be killed.
The Watchers built the device to lock tight its kingdom, bringing with them the
blade - 'Starforge'. A weapon to give the Elder eternal rest. But the Shade...
I must find a way to put a stop to it before it finds a path to freedom..."

"...I've spent every waking hour since, trying to find a way to end this unholy Elder.
Within my secret study, I've begun work on a device of my own, tinkering and shaping.
When I'm finished, this Elder will never bother our world again.
The creature cannot be killed, but maybe... it can be exiled..."

"...Lack of progress on the device has given the High Templar cause for suspicion.
Clapped in irons, I was lead off to the Theopolis prisons for my insubordination.
I must find my way from these chains at all costs. The Elder is coming for us.
Only I can save us from this blasphemy that will soon befall Oriath..."

"...Venarius, that bastard... he marched me through the streets.
His men beat me within an inch of death... I... I told him everything. 
He demanded that I take all of us into the dreamlands, to meet with the Elder.
Using the device, we stepped through, setting foot in the Atlas of Worlds..."

"...It wasn't long before we were met by the Shade itself.
The very essence of the Elder, demanding of me in visions to
tell it why I had returned. But before I could answer,
Venarius stepped forward and greeted the phantom..."

"...Before we knew it, we stood at the base of that blasphemous effigy.
"Pull the sword from my chest." The Elder imposed, and Venarius didn't hesitate.
The earth shook in the face of the Elder's reunion with its body. The true scope of the
Elder befell the High Templar and his men, and as it began to feed, I began to run..."

"...I fear this to be the end. Not just the end for me, but the end of all things. 
The Elder has been freed. Soon it will feast on me... on the rest of the world.
It was too late for me. The Elder had to be stopped. I knew of the shaping powers.
Only I could have a hope at defeating the Elder..."
I spent my life shining a light on truth...\r\nbut some things should remain in darkness,\r\nlocked away for all eternity.
Be not stirred by the Void.
Let madness take control.
Where the body's limits begin,\r\nthe mind's limits end.
Blurred is the boundary\r\nbetween creator and destroyer.
A weapon born of nothingness,\r\ncan only create more nothingness.
Even emptiness may be harnessed.
The First of the Deep was the First of All.\r\nIt was He who conquered the waves,\r\nwho stood guard as land rose from sea.
When the rains come, we cower beneath shelter.\r\nThe First of the Deep teaches us\r\nthat we should seek no shelter but ourselves.
The stone that stays in the waves soon crumbles to sand.\r\nThe First of the Deep teaches us to watch the tides\r\nand choose our moments to move wisely.
When the land rose above the sea, The First of the Deep did not move.\r\nWhen the sky turned to fire, The First of the Deep did not perish.\r\nWe must remember our place, and play to our strengths.
A general may carry his men to greatness, \r\nor be dragged beneath the mire by their burden.
The First of the Plains was the First of the Hunt\r\nIt was she who showed us that there is honour\r\nin waiting in the shadows and picking your moment.
\"Attempt #120: the prototype has finally achieved power similar to the original\r\nwithout breaking all the bones of the test subject. A rousing success.\"
It is a fool who strikes the turtle's shell.\r\nThe First of the Plains teaches us to exploit weaknesses,\r\nand where no weakness can be found, to create one.

A hungry beast wastes no energy. 
Every strike, no matter how small, must work towards victory.
The First of the Plains teaches us 
that the largest prey can still be whittled away.
A secret is a weapon your enemies do not have.\r\nWhen the First of the Plains hunted, she moved in silence and acted quickly.\r\nTo do otherwise is to arm your foes.
When the inferno spread across the land,\r\nit was the First of the Sky who singed his feathers\r\nas he brought the flames to a standstill.
The First of the Sky was the Last of the First.\r\nIt was he who showed us that our limits are self-imposed,\r\nthat what we take for law may just be an illusion.
A bird, too heavily laden, cannot take flight.\r\nThe First of the Sky teaches us to put aside our possessions\r\nso that we may live more freely.
Though we are individual, we share the same plight.\r\nThe First of the Sky teaches us that unity and selflessness,\r\nnot division and greed, is what will carry us upwards.
The First of the Night was the first explorer\r\nIt was she who first braved night's terrors\r\nand found comfort in silence and solace.

A hunter uses everything at their disposal.
The First of the Night did not hold back her venom. 
She used it to weaken her enemies, 
and used her enemies to strengthen her many children.
A burden shared is a burden made lighter.\r\nThe First of the Night teaches us that our burdens \r\nare not just ours to bear, but ours to use against oppressors.

When the fires spilled out of the mountain, The First of the Night wove a net\r\nand was carried into the night on its hot winds.\r\nThough we cannot live without danger, we can learn to live with it.
Gleeful are the few\r\nwho bask in the blood of the many.
When it comes to finding a use for surplus,\r\na rich man has within himself\r\nboundless creativity.
\"Better... stronger... more vital... and then... failure. Always, failure.\r\nWhat key fundamental secret are we missing?\"
When your skin sloughs, and your blood cooks,\r\nyou'll wish the lightning strike had killed you.
What started as a desire to feed\r\nbecame a desire to learn...
Great works take time.\r\n\r\n<default>{This item can be transformed on the Altar of Sacrifice along with Vial of Dominance}
A plan without a deadline stays a plan.
From the flesh of the gods, Xibaqua was born.\r\nFrom the carnage of Xibaqua, we were born.\r\nIt is our duty to return to the gods what was once theirs.
Give him your body, and your burdens will follow.

Destined for sacrifice,
they were dressed in garments
that blurred the lines between this world
and the next.
The seed of life, saved and savoured.\r\n\r\n<default>{This item can be transformed on the Altar of Sacrifice along with Vial of Sacrifice}
We are incapable of change without sacrifice, for we are both the iron and the forge.
We are born raw and untested, and we are shaped by life.\r\n\r\n<default>{This item can be transformed on the Altar of Sacrifice along with Vial of Transcendence}
Though the body rots, the spirit lives on.\r\n\r\n<default>{This item can be transformed on the Altar of Sacrifice along with Vial of Transcendence}
Any thought, no matter how fleeting, changes the thinker.\r\n\r\n<default>{This item can be transformed on the Altar of Sacrifice along with Vial of Transcendence}
We are as much shaped by what we do\r\nas what is done to us.
Take comfort knowing that, even in death,\r\nwe may serve our Queen and fuel her empire.
A keen mind sees what others do not,\r\nmakes connections where others do not, \r\nand is dangerous in a way that others are not.
Freedom is for the privileged, even in death.\r\n\r\n<default>{This item can be transformed on the Altar of Sacrifice along with Vial of the Ghost}
\"What care have I for their pain? They're already dead.\"\r\n- Atalui, Vaal Priestess
For the Vaal, the relationship between slave and master\r\nwas as intimate and volatile as that of lovers.

Facing their death,
the mind of a sacrifice
retreats into instinct and madness.

<default>{This item can be transformed on the Altar of Sacrifice along with Vial of the Ritual}
Facing their death,\r\nthe mind of a sacrifice\r\nretreats into instinct and madness.
Only a fool seeks meaning\r\nin a life so fleeting.
Death is your most important duty.\r\nFace it, or curse your bloodline for all eternity.

Through war we found peace. Through death we found advancement.
Our ancestors did not know where their actions would take them.
Are we any better?

<default>{This item can be transformed on the Altar of Sacrifice along with Vial of Fate}
Doryani promises immortality, yet we build great structures, \r\ncarve magnificent works into stone, so a part of us lives onward.\r\nA sign of faithlessness through action.
War is a thriving infection.\r\nIt numbs the heart and eats away at the soul\r\nuntil only emptiness remains.

There the weary multitude of man-kind 
shall turn in their masses into the wide fire, 
where the destroying flame embraces the living, 
some will go up, some down, filled with misery.
\"Lord of Bone, Lord of Flesh, yet all that we can\r\nmaster turns to ash.\" \r\n- Researcher Arn

"Great minds wish to reveal all the secrets of time and space.
But it does not matter. Creation, the act of Matter Metamorphosis, 
is the only secret worth discovering." 
- Zeel, Vaal Tinkerer
An Emperor must conquer his own darkness\r\nbefore he can act as a beacon of light.

Kaom watched the torches patrol the top of the Watch. 
He observed the lay of the beach, its barricades and rocks, 
and his men in their canoes, ready to lay their lives down for him.
But when his foot hit the sand, he thought only of the fight.

Standing behind iron bars,
Daresso thought of his adoring fans cheering his name, 
his wife's warm embrace waiting for him, 
and of the celebrations that would soon be thrown in his name.
But when the arena gate lifted, he thought only of the fight.

Voll stood at the gates of Sarn, and a nation stood behind him. 
He thought of the righteousness of his cause, 
and of the glory he would bring to the empire he would soon lead. 
But as Chitus and his gemlings advanced, he thought only of the fight.

"No man, before or since,
has climbed to such lofty heights
or fallen so far."
- Voll, Emperor of Purity
\"I don't know how I know, \r\nI just know that I know.\"
When you're on the run,\r\nlook only to yourself for survival.

Xibaqua's treachery was met with divine fury.
One by one, the gods reclaimed their flesh,
until all that remained was a droplet of pure light:
The first Vaal.
So great was the thaumaturgy of a bloodpriest's mark,\r\nthat sacrifices soon welcomed their death.
Death is but the start of your servitude.
We serve only the Night.
There was never a simpler time.\r\nJust simpler motivations.
The leash of the lifegiver\r\nbinds in both directions.
\"One coy look. One blown kiss. One word spoken.\r\nOne night I wish I'd forget.\"
He was a lot luckier before he lost this.

The empire is both the tree and the fruit.
It provides safe harbour as ideas grow within,
and when the time is right, the apple is picked. 
The idea, and our ideals, take root.

Sing with me one last duet,
the curtain closes nigh.
Join me in a quiet song,
Before we all must die.
The greatest of guardians make the greatest of sacrifices.
\"Feel the pain of ancient wounds.\r\nFeel the doom of dying souls.\"
You will know if your subjects follow you from fear\r\nor respect when you have your first moment of weakness.\r\nIf it's the former, they will tear you into pieces like rabid dogs.
It was not his fearlessness or ferocity, nor his tactical genius,\r\nit was his leadership that earned Aul, the Last King, his crown.

Where once had stood a village, lay naught but splinters.
Some had once been her home. 
Some had once been her creations.
Some had once been her family.

<default>{This item can be combined with a Mountain and Valley ring at a Vendor.}

The river, once fertile and fresh, 
and flowing briskly to the sea,
now stood, stained, at a standstill.
Dammed by the coagulating dead.

<default>{This item can be combined with a Meadow and Mountain ring at a Vendor.}

The narrow path turned to rough rocks that led towards the sky.
One last obstacle in a life-long journey
to find a land they could call home.

<default>{This item can be combined with a Meadow and Valley ring at a Vendor.}

Cold winds blasted what little grew on the icy surface.
The gifts of the land lay hidden deeper,
and only patience and persistence would free them.

<default>{This item can be combined with a Mountain and Valley ring at a Vendor.}

Sheltered beneath thick ice,
the river ferried fat fish towards the sea.
But the First King knew the river's secret,
and the fish were not the only ones who grew fat.

<default>{This item can be combined with a Meadow and Mountain ring at a Vendor.}

He surveyed his lands, green and vital,
watched with pride as his slaves quarried fine stone for his fortress,
and thanked the heavens for his many blessings.
But this pilgrimage to the peak was to be his last.

<default>{This item can be combined with a Meadow and Valley ring at a Vendor.}

The fields were silent but for the plucking of fruits,
the rustling of leaves, and the breaking of stone.
No slave dared to speak or look the passing king in the eye.
No one... except Aul.

<default>{This item can be combined with a Mountain and Valley ring at a Vendor.}

With no stone for rebuilding, each storm took its toll on the village.
Huts eventually collapsed, their occupants injured or dead.
Bodies were left by the river, to appease the gods.
But the dead would not remain there.

<default>{This item can be combined with a Meadow and Mountain ring at a Vendor.}
History teaches humility.

In the weeks that followed the Cataclysm,
the dead began to rot and fester.
The air fouled with such concentration,
that passing birds drowned in flight.

Though we live and act as individuals,
in truth, we are tethered together. 
The barriers that divide us need not be broken 
for our spirits to become entangled.
Time, like light, can be refracted into all its myriad colours.\r\nThe first shade is beautiful, but the last will drive the unwary insane.
\"There were no survivors.¬†It had only been fired twice.\"\r\n- Order of the Djinn inscription
\"Fusing the parasite with another ring has manifested unpredictable effects.\r\nI theorise the sacrificial vessel's level of anguish is a key variable.\"\r\n- Arzaak, Syndicate Researcher
A controlled burn is sometimes necessary for new life.
Open the way to new and dangerous lands.
Is it better to find new lands - or to create them?
See the land as it is.
See creation as it was, aflame and frantic.
See creation as it will be, frozen and silent.
See creation as it is, energetic and storming.
There can be no defence against the celestial siblings entropy and time.
\"The form of this replica came to me in a troubled dream.\r\nI do not believe we should ever allow it to be used.\"\r\n- Researcher Arn
What has no siblings but is always a twin?
\"This is one riddle I can't solve.\" \r\n- Researcher Graven
Cold winds whirl at the crown of the world.
In their crimson nightmare, the Vaal are still sacrificing themselves to her glory and beauty. \r\nThey stab their own hearts and cry out in ecstasy, only to rise again.
The spirit hungers for the flesh.
The vastness of the cosmos holds energies beyond comprehension,\r\nshould one have the fortitude to grasp them.
\"We could rival the gods with this power, if only we had the mitigating mechanisms\r\nto make it work. A jewel, a talisman, an armour... or the Font...\"
A tourniquet for the soul, squeezing ethereal into physical.
\"You covet the strength of your peers, mortal?\r\nPerhaps it can be yours, if you are willing to make an offering of their blood...\"\r\n- Vaal Myth of the Third Snake
Exceptional men and women of strong will can flicker a spark, \r\nbut something much greater is needed to unleash the wildfire of true divine flames.
The power of lightning is a power best shared.
The judge determines worthiness by comparison to the paragon: himself.
I condemned an innocent man to the pyres, but to admit this mistake is to condemn myself.\r\nMy only choice is to strive harder.
My subordinates circled me eternally, attuned to the slightest weakness,\r\nready to tear me apart for their own gains.
I sacrificed a life of love for one of responsibility, so that she,\r\nand others like her, might be kept safe.
I was a happy child, before the cruel truth was revealed to me.\r\nI fight so that the children may remain ignorant.
I feel the moral weight of what I must do to protect Wraeclast.\r\nI accept my guilt without shame. It is my gift to humanity.
Strike true, strike hard, and leave no survivors to retaliate.
\"The type Delta test subjects could have escaped with the power offered by\r\nPrototype #15, but they suddenly chose to murder each other instead...\"
Something within the machine never stops moving,\r\nbut Oriathan scholars dare not open it to find out why.
When the time comes to face evil, the faithful are never alone.
Midnight tinkering begets midday murdering;\r\na sinister shaft surreptitiously shot slays a scoundrel.\r\nI will see them again, but not until my work is done.
\"The Midnight Tinkerer's aid was invaluable during our brief alliance,\r\nbut when we failed to make any progress on resurrection, he continued his search elsewhere...\"
The Black Sekhema's trial had only just begun.
The champion's name echoes through time, \r\ndrowning out the whispers of the defeated.

Young Napuatzi was thrown into the pits, an unwilling sacrifice, 
but the offer of her blood was refused.

There exists in every man and woman
a desire to push boundaries, to break new ground,
to make great discoveries,
no matter the personal cost.
Conflict begets only suffering.\r\nFor some, that is by design.
Does the belly swell, or the belt shrink?\r\nTo those caught between, there is no difference,\r\nand something must soon give.
A moment of calm before the battle can end the war.
Winter's white blanket swaddles all.
The Trickster God turned the very Day and Night against each other.\r\nWhat hope have you?
The machines do not hate. They merely serve one who does.
Savour the bitter, cherish the sweet,\r\nFor there may never be another chance to eat.

"Try as I might, I could not escape it.
When I closed my eyes, I saw only death.
Each breath tainted with the scent of seared and smouldering flesh,
And each sound tangled with pleas for mercy."
You can take the girl out of the woods, \r\nbut you can't take the woods out of the girl.
Pain is a fine motivator,\r\nBut if you seek the truth,\r\nFear of pain unknown has no parallel.
As the dead battered Highgate's barricades,\r\nThe Black Sekhema accepted her fate,\r\nAnd stood her ground.
Maids used to threaten to send misbehaving children of\r\nnobility to the pits beneath the Grand Arena.\r\nFor the children of slaves, it was more than just a threat.
Once you begin to rely on your weapons, \r\nYou ensure you can't live without them.
It was a great honour to fight at the front. \r\nThe few that survived the initial charge were guaranteed fame and fortune.
You need not go looking for a second opinion.
If you're going to act like you're better than everyone else, make sure you are.
Only a madman would ignore a god's instructions.
Nothing spreads as quickly as an idea.
How do you defeat that which dwells within you?
Bloodlust begets suffering.
Lightning lives in an endless circle.
WIP
\"We have methods of interrogation the Inquisitors only dream of.\"\r\n- Marcus, Brotherhood Liaison
\"This was the first step in some grand design, \r\nlost to the ages, now ours to decipher.\" \r\n- Dominus, High Templar
The Azmeri must never touch the Tears of Maji, lest Viridi weep.
\"I believed I understood Prototype #112 quite fully, until a test subject\r\nwith Azmeri ancestry donned it. I will be haunted by the results\r\nfor the rest of my life.\"  - Researcher Graven
Under its influence, shards of metal take on a life of their own, wriggling into flesh,\r\nburrowing into organs, and exploding outwards in search of other victims.
Claws open, brace for a bite. Stinger raised, dodge or die.
Imbue the body with stolen spirit, hold the leash tight.
Chitus' success stemmed from his cunning, taking calculated\r\nrisks so that greater dangers could be averted.
An eye for an eye.
The strong survive. The strongest thrive.
The pyre is never wasted on just one heretic.

Death creeps closer; unseen, inexorable, hungry.
A dance as old as time.
Simple. Deadly. Unstoppable.
Lead by example.
He may have returned from the frozen southern reaches,\r\nbut that doesn't mean he ever truly escaped them.
For how little time they had together,\r\ntheir love was all the more powerful.
Every glorious conquest\r\nstands astride innocent bones.
The target changes, but the job's always the same.
Freedom is won only by those who are not free.
Better to act without thought\r\nthan to think without action.
The Goddess abides a kingdom beyond compare,\r\nshould you meet her challenge.
You may appeal to the Goddess for another verdict,\r\nbut justice favours only the truly worthy.
Before the Goddess, nothing remains hidden.\r\nAdversity reveals old flaws and new strengths.
The line that divides hope and fear,\r\nlife and death, crowd and mob,\r\nis as thin as a whisper.
\"This will help with the pain.\r\nOne for you... and one for me.\"\r\n- Doctor 'Shaky Hands' Opden

The sky, the land, the people burned.
What little still stood soon faced wild, battering storms.
Winter arrived suddenly and stayed for a generation.
Civilisation was not simply halted, but reversed, erased.
Somebody does have to get hurt.
All roads lead to that destined doom.
The shadow warrior moves like the wind;\r\nhis strikes land long after he is gone.
The Oriathans built their empire on naval mobility, which allowed\r\nthem to wage war wherever their enemy was weakest.
The giant cares not for the ants.
Expand one single ambition to crystal clarity... and beyond.
To stand at the confluence of the elements,\r\nthe master must achieve perfect balance.
Obtaining information depends upon pretending one already has it.
The lightning fears not the flame.
Maximum power fueled by science gone mad.
Indiscriminate destruction fueled by science gone mad.
Fragile, explosive, and punishing.
Never let the audience know your true form. Misdirect them,\r\nbeguile them. Strike when they least expect it.
The single well-placed arrow that changes the world\r\nmust be preceded by ten thousand practice shots.
Teach a man to burn, and you'll be warm for the rest of his life.
\"Remain poised. Remain balanced. Keep all the emotions of a lifetime caged.\r\nLet only your enemies see the truth of your rage.\"
\"The Faridun cannot earn burial in the sky.\r\nThey have other ways of keeping the dead.\"
\"Allegedly turns water to Lethe. That makes it my competition. \r\nI don't like competition.\"
\"Sap of the Aturi tree, known only to grow at the meeting point of the seven waters.\r\nNothing since its disappearance has smelled as wondrous.\"
\"A symbol of my birthright and claim to my fiefdom. \r\nI must have it if I am to return my family to its rightful place.\"
\"A true curiosity. Matches no known language, yet its illustrations hint at knowledge \r\nonly rediscovered hundreds of years after the death of its unknown author.\"

\"Balabus Arimor was a little-known preacher during the days of Emperor Chitus,\r\nwho believed eternal life could be achieved through ritual sacrifice.\r\nWe shall see whether he was a prophet - or a charlatan.\"
\"As warm as living flesh, and smelling strongly of sulphite.\r\nMorbid curiosity compels me to add it to my collection of oddities.\"
Rubbing the eel's head is said to bring smugglers good fortune.
\"If Jamanra has been resurrected the way so many other ancient heroes have returned,\r\nthen perhaps I can convince him to rise up and unite the Faridun once more!\"
\"Some of my inventions don't live up to their names, but some work all\r\ntoo well. Let's hope that the Unbreakable is the former, not the latter.\"

\"A part of me still believes I can convince Nashta to give up her rebellious ways and come home. That part\r\nof me will forever be nine years of age, futilely chasing her as she runs off into the dunes yet again.\"
\"There can be no freedom\r\nwhile hate still reigns.\"
\"If Admiral Darnaw is stupid enough to send orders to his fleet members \r\nand not expect us to steal them, then he deserves what's coming to him!\"
\"The Vox speak in threats.\r\nWe will answer them with action.\"
Each blow of the hammer shapes the ingot,\r\neach strike stretching and sharpening;\r\nThe sabre's tip reaching out, grasping for life.
Quenched, the blade hardens, becomes brittle.\r\nThe edge will not last forever,\r\nBut when it breaks, its service will continue.

Her apprentice spends hours working the steel,
and the end result is melted for scrap.
Each one made better than the last.
Each one made more quickly.
She knows the path well.
Horrific experiments with corrupted flesh require careful management.
Beyond the veil of death, there burns a fire\r\nby whose light night is borne.
A sacrifice of blood calls forth His vengeance.\r\nLet the righteous become the Hand of God.
The burden falls heaviest not on those that died,\r\nbut on those that did not.
\"Her sisters eternally fought for that shining apex in the skies,\r\nbut Viridi instead found strength in humility.\"\r\n- Azmerian Creation Myth
\"That bronze girl sure knows how to cut someone down to size!\"\r\n‚Äì Bertrand the Plush
Within each of us exists a being of pure malice,\r\nheld back only by the lies we tell ourselves.
The tortured thinker is made heavier by the weight of his guilt.
The cruel thinker finds glee in torture most precise.
The cowardly thinker's greatest success is simply surviving.
Accept the infection, let it take hold.\r\nThen carry it far and wide.
Primordial rage slumbers, waiting for the call\r\nof the stars to return and swallow the world.
All that was loved, all that was hated -\r\nnaught remains but ash.
Stories of heroism by the victor persist,\r\nfor no one survives to contest them.
\"I found the tomb in the first place, and they had the nerve to empty it without me! \r\nReckon it'll make a fine trophy for my efforts.\"
\"One must, as one should, admire the lasting works of those who came before.\r\nThe Vaal were the uncontested greatest architects until we,\r\nand Matatl soared above their best.\"
\"I believe she was a beautiful maiden. \r\nKind, virtuous and devout through-and-through.\r\nSuch a gift will set me apart from all other suitors.\"
\"Victims of war, the indebted, and the irredeemably shamed\r\nwere to live their lives in servitude. Some rose above their station. \r\nThis individual, it seems, was all but deified.\"
\"Heard if you put a drop of blood in its mouth,\r\nit'll whisper the secrets of immortality.\r\nDoesn't have to be your own blood, does it?\"

"I'll give it to her and tell her
'It once held the reflection of a Queen, and now it will once more.'
Anton can cross the Vastiri on his family fruits 
if he thinks he loves her like I do."
Once cast the reflections of royalty, now worth the sum of its parts.
Ornately adorned and heavier than is practical.
A common figure adorning Vaal ruins, but exquisitely crafted from gold.
The last shimmering face witnessed by many a sacrifice.
Silently keeps innumerable secrets whispered in moments of desperation.
At once horrid and beautiful, awkward and alluring, silly and overwhelmingly mysterious.
Dried blood remains trapped in its many deep grooves.
My inventions, my babies, deserve to be in better hands!
...the blueprints for my Extreme Warmth Beam, my Storm Wooing Rod,\r\nthe Mind Sublimator, and the Unbreakable...!
\"If we can prove Jamanra existed, then the Faridun may have a chance to rejoin the\r\nMaraketh. I, for one, would like to meet my parents. I have many questions...\"
\"There is nothing quite so exquisite as a forced confession. The sufferer will\r\nsay anything to make the pain stop, and that's the point. Guilt is irrelevant.\"
\"It supposedly causes enormous plants to grow from almost any soil. The myth claims we\r\nneed to sacrifice a baby to make it function, but that's a bit grotesque, even for me.\"

\"When hope was but a memory, the twin sister Sekhemas Solerai and Lundara arose to unite the Maraketh.\r\nThey wielded the essence of gold and silver. The Spear is one of the two weapons that forged us.\"
\"Wraeclast is harsh, and the Plains of Vastiri are unforgiving. We Maraketh can\r\nill afford an internal war. We must prove that Nashta is behind these attacks.\"
\"They were me granddaddy's. \r\nCould break into any house as quick and silent as a Cardinal's fart.\"
\"Traitorous scum took the life I could've had. \r\nI ain't usually the forgiving type, \r\nbut I feel in this case that I owe him a little gift.\"
\"Never take credit for another man's work.\"
\"Loved her like she was my own daughter.\r\nI just want to know she's safe.\"
\"Damn near everything I've earned. \r\nWorth every little bit.\"
\"Lost touch with a mate of mine when\r\nhe got recruited into some secret squad.\r\nJust want to see how he's doing.\"
\"Enoch deserved better. \r\nThis is the least I can do.\"
\"Just the usual highly-illegal compounds.\r\nDon't drop them. It's fine if you do, but don't.\"

"I wish I could say this was the first time I've forgotten to restock on this thing. 
I forget what it was, but I'm sure I'll remember by the time we need to get it.
Was it beetles? Bottles? I think it began with 'B'.
Or it had no 'B'."
\"I heard the script will send any who attempt to perform it mad,\r\nbut that other than that, it is very good.\"
\"Make sure it'll fit a small man, or a very large child.\r\nAnd check for stains! Knew a few people who'd use them for-... \r\n...Just check for stains.\"
\"Let's just hope she wasn't wearing it when she wandered into the sea!\"
\"It isn't fair to either of us to keep chasing this dream.\"
\"When you stop viewing someone as a fellow human being,\r\nthere's little you won't do to forward your agenda.\r\nThat is what we're dealing with.\"
\"Selfishness and hate fuel these kidnappings. \r\nIt's time we find who is leading them.\"
\"Darnaw is stupid and confident.\r\nI am certain he will have recorded his misdeeds.\"
\"Fidium's fealty to fairness \r\nmakes him the perfect pawn in my plan.\r\nOur plan. Perfect pawn in OUR plan.\"
\"A symbolic piece of history,\r\nfrom a time when people of all backgrounds\r\nunited against a common enemy.\"
\"An unusual request.\"
\"I won't be bullied.\r\nWe must get Hana back.\"
\"Admiral Proclar wreaked havoc on my smuggling routes for two full decades. Now that he's dead, \r\nit's a matter of thieves' honour to check whether my product was in his pipe.\"
\"The chalice holds certain properties that make scientists quite possessive and irrational.\r\nIt's best if you don't ask too many questions about this one.\"
\"At first glance, this seal seems no more than an ornament. But when one\r\nlooks closer, one realizes the design is from no culture we yet know of.\"
\"In the early days of his religion, Innocence told his followers to drink of his blood and\r\nenjoy eternal life. If that power holds in his ancient ichor, I hope that it can resurrect as well.\"
\"This unassuming rock reportedly fell from the sky a few centuries ago. Sounds impossible,\r\nbut the men who are guarding it obviously believe the tale, so I do, too.\"
\"A simple ornament from the days when Keth's trade empire was the\r\nglory of the world. Protectors at the massive toll gates wore these.\"
\"There are very few devices in this world that can act as a heart for a\r\nmachine. This one is an ancient remnant of the work of Vaal engineers.\"
\"I currently possess four-hundred and forty-four pieces of this ancient\r\nand puzzling device. A few seem to be missing. This part is crucial.\"
\"There is no telling what this device may do when completed, but I\r\nhave made it my life's work. There must be a deeper meaning!\"
\"I have spent my family's entire fortune in the pursuit of this device.\r\nAssembling it and turning it on is all I have left.\"
\"My schematics are clear. Once the Enigmatic Assembly is complete, it\r\nwill be a weapon to rival the gods! It must be... it has to be...\"
\"The Eldritch Blade is one half of a pair. Together, the two are said to drive men\r\ninsane by revealing the truth of the world to them. I wish to know this truth.\"
\"Caspiro was a master of presentation. He maintained peace in Wraeclast through displays\r\nof strength that, sadly, had no meaning to the dark presence that dismembered him...\"
\"Trust in scientists to create tools for better drug distillation. They don't know the\r\nworth of the beautiful tools they have. Let's make sure it stays that way.\"
\"Long ago, a traitor was promised this mythical elixir. We consider her a fool for\r\nbelieving it exists, but if it does... I would certainly like to take a sip and find out.\"
\"The lamp is said to contain Aziza, the Fourth Servant of Water. I doubt the tale\r\nis true, but I cannot allow one of our artifacts to fall into Kondor's hands.\"
\"The relief depicts some sort of forgotten Maraketh goddess. I have no idea what\r\nthe context is. The important thing is that you steal it before Bazira does.\"
\"It is said that the Golden Ibis was forged before time itself, before writing, or even\r\noral history. That's nonsense, of course, but it's still very old, and therefore noteworthy.\"
\"The world is governed by certain natural laws. Science and thaumaturgy are one\r\nand the same. But the crystal... it shouldn't exist. It's not from here. We must have it.\"
\"Are we the only ones who understand the danger? The fools! Living ice absorbs heat\r\nand grows. We must control it properly, lest it spread across all of Wraeclast.\"
\"I have a suspicion that the Maraketh Sekhema of legend, Lundara, is the same historical\r\nfigure as the Azmeri and Eternal goddess Lunaris. The Seal may prove that.\"

\"The relief was the first ever depiction of some Maraketh girl named Orbala undertaking her\r\nfifth great adventure. I don't particularly care about the story, I just don't want Bazira to have it.\"
\"My accursed father owes his children this heirloom. We deserve\r\nto know our culture, just like you full-blooded humans do.\"

\"It is my belief that Solerai, from the Maraketh legend, is Solaris herself in another system of\r\nmyths. If I can prove that, I can begin piecing together a true history of the Winter of the World.\"
\"The history of the order of Sin Eaters is shrouded in secrecy and shame.\r\nNevertheless, history demands truth, even if it takes centuries to be revealed.\"
\"Those Eternal bastards looted everything that wasn't bolted to the floor when we\r\nfinally drove them from our island! That candelabra belongs with us!\"
\"By all accounts, the Sword of the Inverse Relic was found aged and rusted,\r\nbut is becoming less weathered over time. We really must study its properties.\"
\"If the skull is real, and not a forgery, then it may show that my people are not the\r\nabominations others believe us to be. The word 'human' may have a broader meaning.\"
\"A great fire once swept the land, and our leaders were turned to ash where they stood.\r\nThe urn contains exactly what you think it does, and serves as proof of our long lineage.\"
Only the souls trapped within can bear witness to the Maven's dark proclivities, and they dare not speak up.
It would be foolish to obey the Maven's demands.\r\nIt would also be foolish not to.
For those who must not endure it,\r\nthere may be found a perverse joy \r\nin watching the struggle for survival.
Precious and perilous,\r\nTantalising and terrible.
\"The village was locked within its walls,\r\nprotected from those who could do them harm,\r\nprotected from those who could save them.\"

"Believing them to have discovered new lands,
they planted their flag in the dirt and called it their own.
A gesture not taken with a great deal of pleasure
by those who already dwelt there."
\"The first explorers took to the hills to discover the lay of the land,\r\nand watched with wonder as the land undulated, crashed and twisted.\"
\"Atop the highest peaks, the sunlight pierced but did not warm.\r\nThe air choked and did not nourish.\r\nAnd those that made the trek realised the folly of their desire for greatness.\"
\"Where once a mountain stood there was now but fields and dust.\r\nOne by one, the stones were moved and placed with intention,\r\nthe consequences borne by the destination and the origin.\"
\"The Shade walked the land with no end in sight,\r\nno purpose in mind,\r\nbut the one it invented to pass the time.\"

"There were seasons in this strange new place, but not of sun and snow.
Seasons of stone that rose and fell like waves.
Seasons of structure and growth and madness and chaos.
Seasons of birth and decay that seemed untethered to cause."

"For a time, it was thought this place could seed an empire
greater than any in history.
The lands could be tamed, and commanded, they thought.
But control, like all things in that place, was an illusion."
\"Grand plans were laid for a place called Atzoatl, though fierce bickering between its Architects is said to have stifled its development.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Research Report
The Banished Architect sought to employ all the\r\ndarkest secrets of the Vaal... at the same time.
The first Karui born on the fringes of the Vaal empire\r\ndeveloped a blood fever born of corruption.
Their three serpentine heads found unity in balance.
The High Priests ensured the loyalty of their slaves by habituating\r\nthem to narcotic stimulants with lethal withdrawals.
Man retains sanity and strives toward civilisation\r\nonly under the blessed veil of ignorance.
Crush your enemies with your essence, so that you may drink of theirs.
Bow before her... or suffer the most gruelling death imaginable.
The priest that carried Yaomac's sigil was\r\ngranted one boon by each serpentine head.
Stolen power is still power.
The Hated Slave seeks dominion over his own kind.
The Sovereign of the Well seeks dominion over the light.
The Blackblooded seeks dominion over darkness itself.
The Liege of the Lightless seeks dominion over the surface dwellers.
The dance of metal and flesh never ends.
You shall be weighed and measured. You shall be judged...\r\nand perhaps you shall be found worthy.
\"The Order tried for centuries to shield the world from chaos.\r\nBut chaos is natural. It is a tool, like any other, with which to\r\nshape our destinies.\" - The Lifegiver's Manifesto
\"Atzoatl was a locus of Corruption, a temple dedicated to the worship of the unspeakable.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Eroded Vaal Orb

\"When the Vaal discovered power could be gained from sacrificing the living, Atzoatl became a death march for the lower classes.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Obsidian Sacrificial Knife
\"In their paranoia, the Architects of Atzoatl hoarded wealth beyond any reasonable measure.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Vaal Golden Idol
\"Doryani himself conducted gem research at Atzoatl in its final days. What brilliant discoveries were lost with that temple?\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Third Ciphered Tablet
\"Much could be learned from the relics said to be kept in Atzoatl. We consider the Vaal ancient, so what did they consider ancient in turn?\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Vaal Mural
\"Evidence suggests that Atzoatl's influence grew great enough that Atziri herself moved her seat of power to within its walls.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Royal Decree cast in Bronze
\"Atzoatl played host to the Cult of the Purple Flame. I do not know what powers they worshipped, but my educated guesses leave me shaken.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Embalmed Claw

\"The Architects intended to research supposed 'Obelisks Beyond Time,' but the Vaal fell before the first obtained monolith was so much as measured.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Crystal Shard

\"Trade with lesser cultures, such as the Maraketh and the early Karui, resulted in overflowing vaults full of golden trinkets and elegant jewels.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, 'Dekhara's Resolve'

\"In its last days, the Architects of Atzoatl became increasingly obsessed with fictional lands. Wondrous lands, by their description, but fictional. Very odd.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Unidentified Angular Device

\"Zantipi is said to have spent most of his considerable talent devising ambushes that used the promise of treasure as a lure for would-be looters.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Broken Locking Mechanism

\"Merchant carvings of the era consistently reported that the Architects could alter the weather in manners terrifying and incomprehensible.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Trade Record Tablet
\"The Vaal were said to have experimented with fire at Atzoatl, though to what end is unknown.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Charred Parchment
\"The Architects apparently sought to master lightning. They may have succeeded just before the fall.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Copper Detritus

\"Their engineering knowledge may have rivaled that of the modern world. The fall of the Vaal no doubt set humanity back a thousand years.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Ancient Gear Interlock

\"A great many warriors were stationed at Atzoatl, ostensibly due to repeated invasion by something referred to as 'a haunting death.'\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Carved Interment Records
\"A great many creatures were bred at Atzoatl, ostensibly due to repeated invasion by some kind of horrifying murderous entity.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Fossilized Egg Sac

\"At the height of their civilization, the Vaal took to ritual combat to solve all of their disputes. As a result, their surviving warriors were among the best in history.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Rust-coated Sword
\"The heart of Atzoatl imbued its denizens with vigour, according to the myths.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Glowing Stone

\"Expedition logs suggest quite a few explorers sought Atzoatl over the centuries. The Architects planned against this potential plundering, however, with ingenious and lethal traps.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Corroded Spring Mechanism
\"The Architects were certainly fond of their ghost stories. The tales almost sound as if the business was taken literally.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Carved Fable

\"The Vaal had little concern for the externalities of their engineering. The toxins produced by their manufacturing may have poisoned the entirety of Atzoatl.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Desiccated Corpse of a Vaal Citizen
\"The Architects sought immortality... perhaps they reside within Atzoatl still...\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Vial of Emerald Water
\"Atzoatl was a place of crude alchemy rather than art.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Urn of Unstable Powder
\"Armour crafted at Atzoatl became the envy of the known world.\" - Icius Perandus, Antiquities Collection, Ancient Metals

Of ash and avalanche,
in storm and flesh,
we dream of unity.
The time approaches...
It isn't the twisted transformative power of corruption that makes it so dangerous.\r\nIt is its ability to hide in plain sight.
